name: THE POWER OF WATER
description: #1 in my water exploration series. According to Theodor Schwenk anthroposophist, engineer and water researcher 1910 - 1986, water is not only a key substance in the creation of life but has such sensible abilities that it enables it to be the core sense organ of our entire planet. The formative forces guides the water to always fold itselves into a spherical shape or a vortex, allowing it to mold and shape all of living natures countless spiralling structures and intervowen streams.
